--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
PREAMBLE
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

This license governs the use, reproduction, modification, and distribution of
the software and associated documentation files (the "Software") released under
it. It is offered freely to humanity as a contribution to beneficial knowledge,
in the tradition of Islamic civilization's long service to science, mathematics,
engineering, and the common good.

The authors of this Software are Muslims who believe that all human action
carries moral weight before Allah, the Creator and Sustainer of all things. We
further believe that providing a tool which is then used to cause harm to human
beings is a matter we are accountable for, even if the harm is caused by another
hand. The Prophet Muhammad, peace be upon him, said: "Whoever calls to guidance
will have a reward equal to the rewards of those who follow him" (Sahih Muslim,
2674). We extend the same principle in reverse: we do not wish to be callers,
even indirect ones, to harm.

This is not a license that attempts to codify the entirety of Islamic law
(Shariah) — a task that would be impossible in a legal instrument of this kind,
and that would require the ongoing interpretive work of qualified scholars across
countless situations. Rather, this license identifies a specific and narrow set
of use cases that are prohibited by near-universal consensus among scholars of
the four Sunni legal schools (Hanafi, Maliki, Shafi'i, and Hanbali), as well as
mainstream Shia jurisprudence, and which are also recognizable as serious ethical
violations across many non-Islamic ethical traditions.

We release this Software in a spirit of openness and benefit to all people. The
restrictions below are not expressions of hostility toward any person or group.
They are an expression of our accountability before Allah and our commitment to
the principle found in the Quran, Surah Al-Ma'idah (5:2):

    "And cooperate in righteousness and piety, but do not cooperate
     in sin and aggression."

We invite all users of this Software — Muslim and non-Muslim alike — to consider
the ethical weight of what they build with the tools available to them.

